                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Mark it with a readonly flag then. ;)  Is it 'const' or 'readonly'?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/State/Host.interface.yaml",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Geissler",
                        "email": "geissonator@yahoo.com",
                        "username": "geissonator"
                    },
                    "message": "I think readonly, in that the PSM firmware will come up and then fill in the supported values for the system."
                },
                {
                    "file": "yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/State/Host.interface.yaml",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Isn't that const then?  ie. once the object is created the values shouldn't change."
                },
                {
                    "file": "yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/State/Host.interface.yaml",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Geissler",
                        "email": "geissonator@yahoo.com",
                        "username": "geissonator"
                    },
                    "message": "Oh, to me const is when you define it in this file or it's hard coded somewhere in code. Yes, they will be created on startup of the PSM app based on meson build features and never change. I'll make it const."
                },
                {
                    "file": "yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/State/Host.interface.yaml",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Geissler",
                        "email": "geissonator@yahoo.com",
                        "username": "geissonator"
                    },
                    "message": "Done"
                },
                {
                    "file": "yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/State/Host.interface.yaml",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "At a dbus level, 'const' basically means \"this property has no need to emit signals because it can't change\"."
                },
                {
                    "file": "yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/State/Host.interface.yaml",
                    "line": 26,
                    "reviewer": {
